******
[1] Kazakhstan (South)
Date: Fri 4 Sep 2009
Source: today.kz News Service [translated by AS, edited]
<http://www.today.kz/ru/news/kazakhstan/2009-09-04/beshenstvo>


Rabies cases notified in South Kazakhstan
-----------------------------------------
The Ministry of Emergency Situations of Kazakhstan has announced that
local doctors diagnosed 2 cases of rabies in the South Kazakhstan
Oblast last Tuesday [1 Sep 2009].

The 1st case occurred in the Abayskoe Region of Shimkent where a
72-year-old man was admitted to the hospital with symptoms of rabies.
3 people who had been in contact with the victim are now under
medical observation.

A similar case has been has been notified in the village of Karatobe
in the Sayrmskoe Region. The victim in this case was an 80-year-old
man. Anyone who had been in contact with the victim is now under observation.

The circumstances of infection, the sources of infection and the
conditions of patients have not been announced.

--
